  "texts": [
    "Residual connectionsResidual connections are a fundamental architectural component in deep neural networks proposed by He et al. 50.",
    "These connections are employed to mitigate the vanishing gradient.",
    "The main idea behind residual connections is to add the skip connection between different layers, creating a shortcut path for the gradient during backpropagation.",
    "We adopt the dense layer as the residual connection in the proposed 2DTCDN.",
    "(3) www.nature.com/scientificreports/ X i, j = h m=1 w n X(i -(m -1) • d, j -(n -1) • d) • K d (m, n) Dense layerRecent studies by Zeng et al. 30 and Das et al."
